# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Security Notes
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# 1. NEVER commit .env to git (it's in .gitignore)
# 2. Use test/sandbox credentials for development:
#    - Stripe: sk_test_... (not sk_live_...)
#    - Namecheap: Sandbox mode if available
# 3. Rotate credentials regularly (every 90 days recommended)
# 4. Use different credentials for dev/staging/production
# 5. Store production credentials in a secret manager:
#    - AWS Secrets Manager
#    - Azure Key Vault
#    - HashiCorp Vault
# 6. Enable 2FA on all service accounts
# 7. Restrict API key permissions to minimum required scopes
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
